                  </hi>. I keep a coffee-shop, in St. John-street—the prisoner was in my service six weeks, and left without giving me notice. On 28th Jan., when I went to bed, I missed my watch, two seals, and a key, off the mantel-shelf, which were safe when I got up in the morning—the prisoner was brought by the policeman on 4th Feb.—he said he was very sorry for what he had done—these (<hi rend="italic">produced</hi>) are my watch, seals, and key—the prisoner had been sent to my room in the morning—I saw him come down.</p>
